gomodel:SYNGO_2092  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.4A: \"USP8 is present in all fractions and is notably abundant in postsynaptic density fractions (Fig. 4A)\"\n\nFig.4B: \"We also found that, in a subpopulation of neurons, USP8 was located in punctate clusters and colocalized with the postsynaptic density protein PSD-95 (Fig. 4B), suggesting that it may function at synapses\"\n\nMoreover, the postsynaptic localization of USP8 is supported by the ubiquitination of postsynaptic AMPARs involved in synaptic transmission.. Experimental description: \"Rat dissociated hippocampal or cortical neurons from postnatal day 1 pups...\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2094-7491" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4419-210X" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1190-4481" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9848-0262" ;
        dc:date           "2018-02-08" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2092" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

